Cingulomania (pronounced sing-yoo-loh-MAY-nee-uh) is a rare, psychologically expressive term that describes an intense desire to be held or hugged. Derived from Latin, ‚Äúcingulum‚Äù means belt or girdle‚Äîsomething that wraps or encircles‚Äîand ‚Äúmania‚Äù refers to an obsession or overwhelming urge. While not a clinical diagnosis, cingulomania captures the deep, primal human longing for physical closeness and emotional comfort through touch. It often arises during times of loneliness, stress, or emotional vulnerability, when a simple embrace can feel like the safest place in the world.
